results.name: Number of letters in "old style" Roman numeral representation of n (e.g., IIII rather than IV).
comment: How is this sequence defined for large values? - _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Feb 01 2011

Also, number of abacus pieces moved (i.e., differing from their initial positions) for the expression of n on a Chinese abacus.  A Chinese abacus is also called "suanpan"(CN), "soroban"(JP). - _FUNG Cheok Yin_, Aug 08 2017
link: Nathaniel Johnston, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..3999
Index entries for sequences related to number of letters in n
maple: A092196 := proc(n) return length(convert(n, roman, period=early)): end: seq(A092196(n),n=1..105); # _Nathaniel Johnston_, May 18 2011
